      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">2 September [1881] ¶ Baron Ferd von Mueller ¶ Melbourne ¶ Australia ¶ My dear Baron von Mueller...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.09.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Alfred Selwyn</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Record group 45, vol. 78, p. 347, National Archives of Canada, Ottawa.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Throughout the letter-copy book, the ink has faded badly, making specific words uncertain or illegible; illegible words are marked by […].</p>
               </note>2 September [1881]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg>. Date based on when the Canadian Geological Survey moved its headquarters. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Australia</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Accept my sincere thanks for the copy of your very useful book on extra Tropical plants<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Presumably B81.13.10.</p>
               </note> The copy you have so kindly sent me I would like to keep in my own library both on account of its intrinsic value and as a remembrance of an old friend. But I would also wish to have a copy for our dept. [...]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">About eight words illegible.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Either for purchase or in Exchange for any of the publications of the Canadian Geol Survey which I hope you receive regularly. I have been very busy all summer removing our Museum &amp; headquarters from Montreal, where they have been for nearly forty years, to this the political Capital of the Dominion. In some respects the change will I hope prove beneficial but it involves a great amount of labour and anxiety as well as disruption to my work. Your old aid Mr [Hoffmann] now presides in our laboratory &amp; is doing good work tho' much of his time is occupied in giving information [to the public].</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[...]<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Several words illegible.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> a […] of labour which makes but [little] […] and interferes a good deal with special work. I never hear now from my old Colleagues Newbery &amp; Ulrich,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">James Newbery, Georg Ulrich.</p>
               </note> are they still connected with the Melbourne Museum? I send our reports regularly to the Royal Society of Victoria but receive nothing in exchange. I would be glad to have a set of the Society Transactions for our library &amp; any other Victorian scientific publications. With much kind regards believe me always sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Alfred R. C. Selwyn</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Remember me kindly to Prof McCoy &amp; other [friends]</p>
         </div>
      </body>
